ude violence against persons based on their gender, including women, men, men who have sex with men, and transgender people.6 While the overwhelming majority of those who experience gender-based violence are women, men and transgender people can also be targeted for violence. The scope of this review is, however, restricted to violence against women and girls as a cause and consequence of HIV acquisition. Note on terminology: The studies", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "728049fc-3a6c-4ad4-947f-5f4a0c4667b9": {"__data__": {"id_": "728049fc-3a6c-4ad4-947f-5f4a0c4667b9", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/discussion-paper-linkages-between-violence-against-women-and-hiv-asia-and-pacific", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "Discussion paper: Linkages between violence against women and HIV in Asia and the Pacific", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/discussion-paper-linkages-between-violence-against-women-and-hiv-asia-and-pacific", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "60745c79fd12784319bb565a1a4c1a796fb552379a0c8ad83420fb8da3dea0d8"}, "3": {"node_id": "9596468e-d4ba-441f-b1e3-30a8137a778d", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/discussion-paper-linkages-between-violence-against-women-and-hiv-asia-and-pacific", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "bf799d484d98f982c3ff852714c86a55c195a